Go ‘head marry don’t you wait on me
oh-ah/Go ‘head marry don’t you wait
on me well/Might not want you when
I go free oh-ah/Might not want you
when I go free well
BOY WILLIE
Come on, Doaker. Doaker know this
one.
As Doaker joins in the men stamp and clap to keep time. They
sing in harmony with great fervor and style.
